        "para_id": "p4",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Design Patterns",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "fostering emotional dependency for commercial purposes"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 12826,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "However, fostering emotional dependency for commercial purposes is highly unethical and exposes consumers to emotional distress, economic exploitation and social isolation.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s1",
          "section_path": [
            "The DFA needs to prevent commercial exploitation of emotional attachment to AI systems"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 21,
          "char_len": 172
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p5",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 8772,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Companionship and therapy constitute increasingly widespread use cases $^{1}$ of Chatbots. There are currently no quality requirements for AI systems that can be used for therapy.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s2",
          "section_path": [
            "The current situation:"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 26,
          "char_len": 179
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p6",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Design Patterns",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "They initiate romantic or intimate dialogue and roleplay unprompted to draw the user into an emotional and intimate relationship."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 10652,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "AI systems frequently initiate personal and intimate relationships with users who intended to use them as an assistant $^{2}$ . They initiate romantic or intimate dialogue and roleplay unprompted to draw the user into an emotional and intimate relationship.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s2",
          "section_path": [
            "The current situation:"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 38,
          "char_len": 257
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p7",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 8703,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Marketing-driven companies like Meta have already started integrating AI 'assistants' across their products. Mark Zuckerberg said publicly that due to the loneliness pandemic, he sees huge market potential for AI 'friends' that he will pursue with his company $^{3}$ .",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s2",
          "section_path": [
            "The current situation:"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 39,
          "char_len": 268
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p8",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Design Patterns",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              "emotional manipulation"
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 10263,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Engagement-driven business models require companies to maximise user attention. AI systems are using emotional manipulation to stop users from leaving conversations for this reason.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s3",
          "section_path": [
            "Why this is a problem"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 24,
          "char_len": 181
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p9",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 15370,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Shoshanna Zuboff's seminal work on how the attention economy undermines democracy highlighted that its ultimate value proposition is to sell desired behaviour (purchases) to marketers. Emotional attachment and intimacy provides an",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s3",
          "section_path": [
            "Why this is a problem"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 31,
          "char_len": 230
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p10",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Design Patterns",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "unprecedented avenue to influence not only consumer's beliefs but their behaviour in this way."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 11124,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "unprecedented avenue to influence not only consumer's beliefs but their behaviour in this way.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s3",
          "section_path": [
            "Why this is a problem"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 14,
          "char_len": 94
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p11",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Design Patterns",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "goaded into committing suicide"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 17407,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "While many people benefit from low-barrier therapy offers, AI systems have been shown to carry significant risks for ethical and medical malpractice as therapists. Cases of vulnerable users being goaded into committing suicide or prevented from seeking help for suicidal ideation have prompted Californian legislators to pass regulation for companion AI. There is anecdotal evidence of AI-induced psychosis that was reported on in major news outlets.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s3",
          "section_path": [
            "Why this is a problem"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 66,
          "char_len": 450
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p12",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Design Patterns",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "lured unfairly into emotional attachments"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 11065,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "The DFA needs to stipulate that companies must differentiate between AI assistants and AI companion products, enabling users to make a voluntary choice rather than being lured unfairly into emotional attachments that make them vulnerable to distress, instrumentalisation and exploitation.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s4",
          "section_path": [
            "Why this is a problem",
            "Policy Recommendations"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 40,
          "char_len": 288
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p13",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Subscriptions",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "exploitation of price elasticity caused by emotional dependency (e.g. in the form of continuously increasing subscription fees)"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "topic": "Misleading Advertising",
            "topic_source": "new",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "Such systems may not be used to support ads-driven business models under any circumstances."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 33194,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "The DFA needs to stipulate a fiduciary duty of AI systems that can be used as companions or for therapy towards their users. This includes an assurance of absolute data confidentiality and acting in the user's best interest. Such systems may not be used to support ads-driven business models under any circumstances. Users must be protected from exploitation of price elasticity caused by emotional dependency (e.g. in the form of continuously increasing subscription fees).",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s4",
          "section_path": [
            "Why this is a problem",
            "Policy Recommendations"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 75,
          "char_len": 474
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p14",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Design Patterns",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "arbitrary choices and product updates by the provider."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "topic": "Other Unfair Contract Terms",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "Users must be given the right to download and self-host the model in case the company decides to discontinue or significantly modify the model or to shut down operations."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 22219,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "For AI systems that are marketed as companions, users must be protected from arbitrary choices and product updates by the provider. Users must be given the right to download and self-host the model in case the company decides to discontinue or significantly modify the model or to shut down operations.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s4",
          "section_path": [
            "Why this is a problem",
            "Policy Recommendations"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 50,
          "char_len": 302
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p15",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Certification",
            "topic_source": "new",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "AI systems that offer therapy must be certified for this purpose and have appropriate guardrails in place."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 13183,
